rg/wiki/Phenetics\">taximetrics<\/a> (measurement of an organism's form) rather on the modern <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phylogenetic_tree\">phylogenetic<\/a> (evolutionary relationship) basis for biological taxonomy.<\/p>\n","answer_id":43325,"question_id":43319,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1455473790}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43319/am-i-a-lobe-finned-fish","last_activity_date":1455473790,"creation_date":1455464543,"answer_count":1,"title":"Am I a lobe-finned fish?","body":"<p>I really wish this question only contained the title and tags, but the website forces me to write some text.<\/p>\n","question_id":43319,"tags":["taxonomy","phylogenetics"],"score":-1,"accepted_answer_id":43325,"down_vote_count":3,"closed_reason":"unclear what you're asking","is_answered":true,"view_count":79,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6096c3c1f039c61a79f8f6ec031386c5?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":21837,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21837/allad1n","reputation":6,"display_name":"Allad1n"},"closed_date":1455598225,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f313f37a72b15b1dc4561352400278be?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19593,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19593/mg-md","reputation":104,"display_name":"MG_MD"},"score":0,"post_id":43277,"edited":false,"creation_date":1455296397,"comment_id":74835,"body":"On a cellular level, Meiosis is the mechanism that creates genetic diversity in gametes.  Sexual reproduction, though, is the largest contributing factor to diversity and the catalyst of evolution."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6096c3c1f039c61a79f8f6ec031386c5?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":21837,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21837/allad1n","reputation":6,"display_name":"Allad1n"},"score":0,"post_id":43277,"