ually? Or is a yearly shot necessary because immunity only lasts a year?<br>\n<sup>I might have to re-post this last question at Health.SE as a dedicated question, but since related to above I prefer to leave it here for now. Grab me in chat if need be!<\/sup>    <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","question_id":43252,"tags":["virus","vaccination"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":43253,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":31,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1455224322},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ac830528d90815b0e4f04a771ff46252?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":21341,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21341/user1062760","reputation":120,"display_name":"user1062760"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":3,"post_id":43063,"edited":false,"creation_date":1454764461,"comment_id":74282,"body":"Nope, you are incorrect here. Everey cell carries a complete set of genomic information, it is &quot;only&quot; differently expressed (read out). The only exception are egg and sperm cells, which carry only half a set of chromosomes (23 instead of 46) to be able to combine with their counterpart."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9d93c0899fe05ce22895a7e483b9157b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":18914,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/18914/tusky","reputation":164,"display_name":"Tusky"},"score":0,"post_id":43063,"edited":false,"creation_date":1454767992,"comment_id":74285,"body":"In giving birth, the sex cells join to form a zygote of 23+23 = 46 chromosomes. This zygote contains both the chromosomes. These chromosomes affect a variety of things like gender etc"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgu